newsitem.title: CHINA: Shanghai soybean ends mixed on uncertainty.
newsitem.headline: Shanghai soybean ends mixed on uncertainty.

text.p: Shanghai soybean futures ended mixed on Thursday with heavy liquidation of the November contract, traders said.
The key November 1996 contract ended at 3,342 yuan ($402) per tonne, rising 14 yuan. It opened at an intra-day high of 3,350 and hit a low of 3,321.
January fell 13 to 3,225 yuan per tonne, March rose six to 3,239, May 11 to 3,390, July 20 to 3,380 and September dropped 99 to 3,281.
Combined volume rose sharply to 22,100 tonnes from 6,400.
Traders said investors offset many positions in the November contract while they had little interest in other contracts.
"Some investors offset their positions and moved their money into more active markets due to a lack of market-moving news," one trader said.
"Most investors took a wait-and-see attitude," he added.
Analysts expect soybeans to continue moving in a narrow range in the next few days.
